ResourceHeader.ResourceName: GOES 15 Magnetospheric Electron Detector (MAGED) data with average flux of 40 keV at 1 m Resolution in Spacecraft Coordinates
ResourceHeader.Description: The GOES 15 Magnetospheric Electron Detector (MAGED) are essentially the same as the Energetic Particle Sensor (EPS) on GOES 8-12. For more information, please see T. G. Onsager et al. (1996), Operational uses of the GOES energetic particle detectors, in GOES-8 and Beyond, Proc. SPIE, Vol. 2812, edited by E. R. Washwell, pp. 281-290, Bellingham, WA.  These data file contain mainly information on the electron count rates and fluxes from 5 energy channels from 40-475 keV for all 9 telescopes. Data files contain long descriptive header.
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: NASA-Office of Space Science Applications (United States); NOAA National Environmental Satellite Service (United States); Dr. Terry G. Onsager

AccessURL.Name: Direct access to the GOES 15 Magnetospheric Electron Detector (MAGED) data
AccessURL.Description: Direct link to the GOES 15 Magnetospheric Electron Detector (MAGED) data in CSV format as well as the energetic particle data from other GOES spacecraft. The data are sorted by year, month, spacecraft, and file type. The file names indicates the data type, spacecraft number, year, month, and resolution. For example, g15_maged_19me15_1m_20110101_20110131.csv, indicates goes 15 magnetometer data at 1 m resolution from start of January 01, 2011 to the end of January 31, 2011.

AccessInformation.Acknowledgement: NASA; NOAA; Dr. Terry G. Onsager

TimeSpan.Note: Data file may fill out the first month and last month with flags. Time format in data files is year-month-day hour:minute:seconds.
